  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The television production studio and media services of the University of Michigan, commonly referred to as "Michigan Media."</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">It was formed in 1978 through the merger of the university Television Center and the university Audio-Visual Education Center. The Television Center began producing educational programs for broadcast on commercial and public stations in 1950. The Audio-Visual Education Center produced films for the university and operated a film distribution library. The Media Resources Center closed in 1986.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
